# Common Library (`common-lib`) — Full Documentation

> **Component Type:** Shared Java Library (JAR)
> **Group:** `com.itways` | **Artifact:** `common-lib` | **Version:** `1.0.0`
> **Java:** 21 | **Spring Boot:** 3.2.2 | **Build Tool:** Maven

---

## 1. High-Level Overview

`common-lib` is a **shared utility library** that all microservices in the **AI Assistant Platform** depend on. It is **not** a standalone runnable application — it is packaged as a JAR and imported as a Maven dependency.

Its purpose is to centralize **cross-cutting concerns** so that every microservice doesn't re-implement the same logic. Think of it as the *"foundation layer"* that every service in the platform stands on.

**What it provides:**

| Capability              | Enable Annotation        | What You Get                                          |
|-------------------------|--------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------|
| Core Utils & API Standards | `@EnableCommon`       | Unified API responses, global exception handling, Swagger config, error codes |
| Security & JWT          | `@EnableCustomSecurity`  | JWT generation/validation, authentication filters, `@AccountId` injection, API Key authentication |
| RSA Encryption          | `@EnableEncryption`      | RSA-based encrypt/decrypt for sensitive data (PII, passwords) |
| Caching                 | `@EnableCache`           | Abstracted caching via Ehcache or in-memory, configurable per-cache TTL |
| Notifications           | `@EnableNotifications`   | RabbitMQ-backed notification publishing (Email, SMS, Push) |
| Templating              | `@EnableFreeMarker`      | FreeMarker template rendering from files or raw strings |

**Key Design Decision:** Features are opt-in via custom `@Enable*` annotations. A service only activates the modules it needs — no bloated startup or unnecessary dependencies.

