### 3.2 — `common` (Core Utilities & API Standards)

Activated by `@EnableCommon`. This is the most basic module and should almost always be enabled.

#### `ApiResponse<T>` — Unified API Response Wrapper

Every REST endpoint in the platform returns data wrapped in this:

```java
{
    "timestamp": "2025-01-15T10:30:00",
    "status": "success",      // or "error"
    "message": "Operation completed successfully",
    "data": { ... },          // actual payload (null on error)
    "errorCode": null         // null on success, e.g. "AUTH_001" on error
}
```

**Factory methods:**

```java
// Success
ApiResponse.success(myData);
ApiResponse.success("Profile updated", myData);

// Error
ApiResponse.error("Invalid credentials", ErrorCodes.INVALID_CREDENTIALS);
```

#### `PageResponse<T>` — Pagination Wrapper

Standard pagination fields used across all list endpoints:

```java
PageResponse<User> page = PageResponse.<User>builder()
    .content(userList)
    .pageNo(0)
    .pageSize(20)
    .totalElements(150)
    .totalPages(8)
    .last(false)
    .build();
```

#### `GlobalExceptionHandler` — Centralized Error Handling

A `@RestControllerAdvice` that catches and formats errors into `ApiResponse`:

| Exception Type | HTTP Status | Error Code |
|---|---|---|
| `BusinessException` | Custom (from exception) | Custom (from exception) |
| `MethodArgumentNotValidException` | 400 | `VALIDATION_ERROR` |
| Any other `Exception` | 500 | `INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR` |

#### `CustomErrorController` — Framework-Level Error Handling

Catches errors that happen *outside* Spring MVC (e.g., 404 for missing paths, filter-level errors).
Returns the same `ApiResponse` format so clients always get a consistent JSON structure.

#### `ErrorCodes` — Shared Error Code Constants

Centralized error codes used across all services:

```java
ErrorCodes.INVALID_CREDENTIALS  // "AUTH_001"
ErrorCodes.USER_NOT_FOUND       // "AUTH_002"
ErrorCodes.RESOURCE_NOT_FOUND   // "RES_001"
ErrorCodes.VALIDATION_ERROR     // "VAL_001"
ErrorCodes.INTERNAL_ERROR       // "SYS_001"
ErrorCodes.UNAUTHORIZED         // "AUTH_401"
ErrorCodes.FORBIDDEN            // "AUTH_403"
ErrorCodes.BAD_REQUEST          // "REQ_001"
// ... and more (OTP, CAPTCHA, ACCOUNT_LOCKED, etc.)
```

#### `BusinessException` — Base Exception

Throw this from services when a business rule is violated:

```java
throw new BusinessException("Email already exists", ErrorCodes.USER_ALREADY_EXISTS, 409);
throw new BusinessException("Account locked", ErrorCodes.ACCOUNT_LOCKED, 423);
```

#### `InvalidApiKeyException` — API Key Specific Exception

Pre-built exception for invalid API keys (extends `BusinessException`, returns **401**).

#### `SwaggerConfig` — OpenAPI / Swagger UI

Configures Swagger with:
- Title: *"AI Assistant API Platform"*
- Bearer JWT authentication scheme
- Auto-applied to all endpoints

#### `RefGenerator` — Transaction Reference Generator

Generates unique reference IDs (e.g., for OTP sessions):

```java
@Autowired
private RefGenerator refGenerator;

String ref = refGenerator.generate("OTP", 12);
// Output: "OTP7A3B4C5D6E8F"
```

#### Shared DTOs

- **`IntentResult`** — Represents AI intent classification results (intent name, confidence score, entities, original text, reasoning).
- **`Template`** — Represents a notification/email template record (id, name, type, content, description, allowFailure, timestamps).

