### 3.5 — `cache` (Caching Abstraction)

Activated by `@EnableCache`.

#### Architecture

```
CacheStoreFactory (interface)
├── EhcacheStoreFactory (production)  ──► EhcacheStore (wraps Ehcache)
└── MemoryStoreFactory  (dev/test)    ──► MemoryStore  (ConcurrentHashMap + manual TTL)

CacheStore<K, V> (interface)
├── put(key, value)
├── get(key) → Optional<V>
├── containsKey(key) → boolean
├── remove(key)
├── remove(key, value) → boolean  (conditional)
└── clear()
```

#### Provider Selection

Controlled by `itways.cache.provider` property:

| Value | Factory | Default? |
|---|---|---|
| `ehcache` | `EhcacheStoreFactory` | ✅ Yes (matchIfMissing) |
| `inmemory` | `MemoryStoreFactory` | No |

#### Configuration

```properties
# Select provider
itways.cache.provider=ehcache

# Global defaults
itways.cache.ehcache.heapSize=1000       # max entries
itways.cache.ehcache.ttlMinutes=10       # default TTL
itways.cache.ehcache.resetTtlOnUpdate=false

# Per-cache overrides
itways.cache.caches.otp.ttlMinutes=5
itways.cache.caches.otp.heapSize=500
itways.cache.caches.mfa-tokens.ttlMinutes=2
itways.cache.caches.mfa-tokens.heapSize=200
```

#### Usage in Services (Programmatic)

```java
@Autowired
private CacheStoreFactory cacheStoreFactory;

// Get a pre-configured cache
CacheStore<String, String> otpCache = cacheStoreFactory.getCache("otp");
otpCache.put("user123", "482916");
Optional<String> otp = otpCache.get("user123");

// Create an ad-hoc cache with custom config
CacheStore<String, String> myCache = cacheStoreFactory.createCache(
    "session-data", String.class, String.class,
    CacheConfig.builder().ttlMinutes(30).heapSize(500).build()
);

// Or let it auto-configure from properties (or use defaults)
CacheStore<String, String> autoCache = cacheStoreFactory.createCache("my-cache");
```

#### Usage with Spring Annotations

Standard `@Cacheable` / `@CacheEvict` / `@CachePut` also work because `@EnableCache` includes `@EnableCaching`, and a `ConcurrentMapCacheManager` is provided as a fallback `CacheManager` bean.

```java
@Cacheable(value = "users", key = "#userId")
public User getUser(String userId) { ... }
```

#### ExpiryPolicyConfig — Custom TTL Behavior

Controls whether updating a cache entry resets its TTL:
- `resetTtlOnUpdate = false` (default): entry expires based on creation time only
- `resetTtlOnUpdate = true`: every `put()` with the same key resets the TTL countdown

