### 3.6 — `notification` (RabbitMQ Messaging)

Activated by `@EnableNotifications`.

#### RabbitMQ Topology

| Resource | Value |
|---|---|
| Exchange | `notification.exchange` (TopicExchange) |
| Queue | `notification.queue` (durable) |
| Routing Key | `notification.routing.key` |

#### `NotificationRequest` DTO

```java
NotificationRequest request = NotificationRequest.builder()
    .recipient("user@example.com")
    .subject("Welcome!")
    .body("<html>...</html>")
    .type("EMAIL")                           // EMAIL, SMS, PUSH
    .metadata(Map.of("userId", "123"))
    .providerConfig(EmailProviderConfig.builder()
        .host("smtp.gmail.com")
        .port(587)
        .username("sender@gmail.com")
        .password("app-password")
        .from("noreply@myapp.com")
        .build())
    .build();
```

#### `NotificationPublisher`

```java
@Autowired
private NotificationPublisher notificationPublisher;

notificationPublisher.sendNotification(request);
// → Message published to "notification.exchange" with routing key "notification.routing.key"
```

The consumer (listener) for these messages lives in a **separate notification service** — this library only handles the *publishing* side.

