## 5. How to Use (Consumer Service)

### Step 1: Add Dependency

```xml
<dependency>
    <groupId>com.itways</groupId>
    <artifactId>common-lib</artifactId>
    <version>1.0.0</version>
</dependency>
```

### Step 2: Enable What You Need

```java
@SpringBootApplication
@EnableCommon               // Almost always needed
@EnableCustomSecurity       // If your service handles authenticated requests
@EnableEncryption           // If you need RSA encrypt/decrypt
@EnableNotifications        // If you publish notifications
@EnableFreeMarker           // If you render email/notification templates
public class MyServiceApplication {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SpringApplication.run(MyServiceApplication.class, args);
    }
}
```

### Step 3: Register `AccountIdArgumentResolver` (if using `@AccountId`)

In your consuming service's `WebMvcConfigurer`:

```java
@Configuration
public class WebConfig implements WebMvcConfigurer {
    @Override
    public void addArgumentResolvers(List<HandlerMethodArgumentResolver> resolvers) {
        resolvers.add(new AccountIdArgumentResolver());
    }
}
```

### Step 4: Configure Properties

Add the required properties for the modules you enabled (see Configuration Reference above).

